contentrichtext.text: '''Rusalka''' may refer to: * [[Rusalka]], a water-nymph in Slavic mythology * [[Rusalka (opera)|''Rusalka'' (opera)]], an opera by Antonín Dvořák * [[Rusalka (play)|''Rusalka'' (play)]], a major though unfinished verse play by Alexander Pushkin ** [[Rusalka (Dargomyzhsky)|''Rusalka'' (Dargomyzhsky)]], an opera by Alexander Dargomyzhsky based on Pushkin's play * [[Rusalka (book)|''Rusalka'' (book)]], a fantasy novel by C.J. Cherryh * [[Rusalka (film)|''Rusalka'' (film)]], a Russian film (2007) by [[Anna Melikian]] * [[Rusalka, Bulgaria]], a resort on the Bulgarian Black Sea Coast * [[Lake Rusałka]], a lake in Poznań, Poland * ''Rusalka'', a song by [[Radarmaker]] * [[Russian monitor Rusalka|''Rusalka'']], a Russian battleship which sank near Helsinki, Finland on September 7, 1893 ** [[Russalka Memorial]] in Tallinn, by Amandus Adamson * [[Rusalka Planitia]], a surface feature of the planet Venus *"Russalka or The Seacoast of Bohema", a short story by Joanna Russ * ''Rusalka'', a Soviet ship from ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops]]''. {{disambig}}
